\title{Hyperbolic Bulk}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{description}{On-chain GF(3) entropy storage via Aptos Move - bulk-boundary correspondence where entropy lives in the interior and observables project to agents}

\subtree{
\title{Hyperbolic Bulk Skill}
\p{\strong{Status}: ✅ Production Ready \strong{Trit}: 0 (ERGODIC - mediates bulk ↔ boundary) \strong{Principle}: AdS/CFT correspondence for entropy \strong{Chain}: Aptos (Move language)}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{The \strong{Hyperbolic Bulk} implements on-chain entropy storage with GF(3) conservation. Named after the AdS/CFT bulk-boundary correspondence:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{BULK} (interior): Entropy records, triads, reafference proofs}
\li{\strong{BOUNDARY} (observable): Agents, skills, colors}
}

\pre{\startverb
         BOUNDARY (Observable)
    ┌─────────────────────────────┐
    │  Agents  │  Skills  │ Colors │
    └─────────────┬───────────────┘
                  │ project
                  ▼
    ┌─────────────────────────────┐
    │      HYPERBOLIC BULK        │
    │  ┌─────────────────────┐    │
    │  │  EntropyRecord      │    │
    │  │  drand ⊕ eeg ⊕ vrf  │    │
    │  └──────────┬──────────┘    │
    │             ▼               │
    │  ┌─────────────────────┐    │
    │  │  EntropyTriad       │    │
    │  │  GF(3) = 0 conserved│    │
    │  └──────────┬──────────┘    │
    │             ▼               │
    │  ┌─────────────────────┐    │
    │  │  ReafferenceProof   │    │
    │  │  predict = observe  │    │
    │  └─────────────────────┘    │
    └─────────────────────────────┘
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Entropy Sources}
\pre{\startverb
| Source | Type | Property |
|--------|------|----------|
| **DRAND** | League of Entropy | Public, verifiable, unpredictable |
| **EEG** | Brainwave bands | Private, embodied, cognitive state |
| **Aptos VRF** | On-chain randomness | Consensus-secured, tamper-proof |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Combination}: \code{\startverb combined = drand_seed ⊕ eeg_seed ⊕ onchain_rand\stopverb}}
}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Conservation}
\p{Triads must sum to 0 mod 3:}

\pre{\startverb
MINUS (-1) ≡ 2 (mod 3)  — Verification/Constraint
ERGODIC (0)             — Coordination/Balance  
PLUS (+1)               — Generation/Exploration

Conservation: trit_1 + trit_2 + trit_3 ≡ 0 (mod 3)
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Strict Mode}: \code{\startverb form_conserved_triad()\stopverb} reverts if not conserved.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Move Contract}
\pre{\startverb
module hyperbolic_bulk::entropy_triads {
    
    struct EntropyRecord has store, drop, copy {
        drand_round: u64,
        drand_seed: u256,
        eeg_seed: u256,
        combined_seed: u256,
        timestamp: u64,
        trit: u8,
        color_hex: vector<u8>,
    }

    struct EntropyTriad has store, drop, copy {
        record_id_1: u64,
        record_id_2: u64,
        record_id_3: u64,
        gf3_sum: u8,
        gf3_conserved: bool,
        skill_1: vector<u8>,
        skill_2: vector<u8>,
        skill_3: vector<u8>,
    }

    struct ReafferenceProof has store, drop, copy {
        seed: u256,
        predicted_color: vector<u8>,
        observed_color: vector<u8>,
        matched: bool,
        loop_type: vector<u8>,  // "loopy_strange" or "exafference"
    }

    #[randomness]
    entry fun store_entropy(...) { /* combines drand ⊕ eeg ⊕ vrf */ }
    
    entry fun form_conserved_triad(...) { /* enforces GF(3) = 0 */ }
    
    entry fun record_reafference(...) { /* proves prediction = observation */ }
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Integration with World-Memory-Worlding}
\pre{\startverb
| Autopoietic Phase | Bulk Operation | Trit |
|-------------------|----------------|------|
| **MEMORY** | `store_entropy()` | -1 |
| **REMEMBERING** | `get_triad()` | 0 |
| **WORLDING** | `form_conserved_triad()` | +1 |
\stopverb}

\p{The loop closes when worlded triads become new memory records.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Reafference Proofs}
\p{On-chain proof that prediction matched observation:}

\pre{\startverb
struct ReafferenceProof {
    seed: u256,
    predicted_color: vector<u8>,
    observed_color: vector<u8>,
    matched: bool,           // prediction == observation
    loop_type: vector<u8>,   // "loopy_strange" iff matched
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Loopy Strange}: Generator ≡ Observer when same seed produces same color.}
}

